
dr_meter is dynamic range meter. In short, it measures how much does the amplitude of music change.
dr_meter is attempt to create open-source, non-GUI, format-agnostic and OS-agnostic dynamic range meter,
whose results will be compatible with TT DR Offline Meter's.


What can I do with it?
Read the LICENSE.


How to use it?
$ make
then pipe raw stereo signed 16-bit little-endian 44100Hz data into it, for example:
$ flac -scd /your/favourite/music.flac | ./dr_meter


Why to use it?
To fight overcompression. Interesting links about loudness wars:
 * http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loudness_war
 * http://turnmeup.org/
 * http://justiceforaudio.org/
 * http://www.pleasurizemusic.com/
 * http://dr.loudness-war.info/

